<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1001
                    The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Secretary of State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1001</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1001</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1001" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1001">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/7–3045:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1001<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-31">July 31
                            [1945.]</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>164. Following telegram (re <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 419, July 30<note n="1" xml:id="d1001fn1">
                        <ref target="#d999">Document No. 999</ref>.</note>) was sent to Stockholm on
                    July 26:<note n="2" xml:id="d1001fn2">As telegram No. 1439.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“<gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> learns (your military attaché’s
                            677 [<hi rend="italic">667</hi>] to <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> July 24<note n="3" xml:id="d1001fn3">
                                <ref target="#d990">Document No. 990</ref>.</note>) Sov Govt will
                            ask Swedish Govt to deliver interned German airplanes to Sov Govt as
                                <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty. Should report be correct
                            it is desirable that you, preferably supported by your British and
                            French colleagues,<note n="4" xml:id="d1001fn4">
                                <persName corresp="#p_JCB1">Cecil Bertram Jerram</persName> and
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CVSCC1">Christian Carra de Vaux de
                                    Saint-Cyr</persName>, respectively.</note> should inform Swedish
                            Govt that we cannot acknowledge such a <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty theory and that Swedish Govt should not therefore
                            permit disposition of German property or equipment as <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty. In our opinion, all German
                            assets and interests are now under the joint jurisdiction of the four
                            occupying powers and should not be removed or disposed of without
                            consent of Allied Control Commission.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
